pipeline_summary.name: AirVisual_Pipeline_Lat_Long_v1
pipeline_summary.description: Extracts air quality data from the AirVisual API using latitude/longitude coordinates, validates the JSON response, and loads it into a PostgreSQL data warehouse with dimensional modeling.

components.name: Extract AirVisual Data
components.description: Fetches current air quality and weather data from the AirVisual API for a specific latitude/longitude, writes the response atomically to a JSON file, and skips processing if a duplicate record already exists in PostgreSQL.

components.name: Validate AirVisual JSON
components.description: Reads the JSON file produced by the extraction step and validates its structure and content before downstream loading.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful extraction of AirVisual data

components.name: Load AirVisual Data to PostgreSQL
components.description: Transforms validated AirVisual JSON into a dimensional model and loads records into PostgreSQL dimension and fact tables with idempotent inserts.
outputs: Rows inserted into dimDateTimeTable, dimLocationTable, dimMainPollutionTable, factairvisualtable

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful validation of the AirVisual JSON

description.default: Extracts air quality data from the AirVisual API using latitude/longitude coordinates, validates the JSON response, and loads it into a PostgreSQL data warehouse with dimensional modeling.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

LATITUDE.description: Latitude coordinate for the AirVisual API request

LONGITUDE.description: Longitude coordinate for the AirVisual API request

timeout.description: Maximum time in seconds to wait for the API response

file_path.description: Path to the JSON file produced by the extraction step

mapping_main_pollution_path.description: Path to the main pollution mapping JSON file

mapping_weather_code_path.description: Path to the weather code mapping JSON file

sources: AirVisual API (nearest_city endpoint) providing current air quality and weather data
sinks: PostgreSQL data warehouse tables: dimDateTimeTable, dimLocationTable, dimMainPollutionTable, factairvisualtable
